        <h3>The Information Knoda Collects</h3>
        <p>Knoda may collect personally identifiable information from Users in a variety of ways.  Personally identifiable information may include, without limitation, (i)&nbsp;contact data (such as a User’s name and e-mail addresses); (ii)&nbsp;demographic data (such as a User’s zip code, age and income); (iii) other account information (e.g., Facebook or Twitter login information); and (iv) other information requested during the account registration process.  If a User communicates with Knoda by e-mail or otherwise, posts User Content (as defined in the Website Terms of Use) to the Website, posts messages to any forums, completes online forms, surveys or entries or otherwise interacts with or uses the features on the Website, any information provided in such communications may be collected by Knoda.  Knoda may also collect information about how Users use the Website, for example, by tracking the number of unique views received by the pages of the Website, geolocation information, or the domains and IP addresses from which Users originate.  While not all of the information that Knoda collects from Users is personally identifiable, it may be associated with personally identifiable information that Users provide Knoda through the Website or otherwise.</p>
        <p>Knoda may use “cookies” or “web beacons” to track how Users use the Website.  A cookie is a piece of software that a web server can store on Users’ PCs and use to identify Users should they visit the Website again.  Users may adjust their web browser software if they do not wish to accept cookies.  Knoda may use third party advertising networks to serve advertisements on the Website.  The cookies received with banner advertisements served by these networks are used to collect and build anonymous behavioral profiles by these companies to deliver targeted advertisements and tracking referrals, and Knoda generally does not have access to this information.</p>
